        <h2>Motivation</h2>

        <p>Motivation is an essential aspect of patients' behavior change, and as health professionals, we often encounter the challenge of evoking motivation in our patients. However, misconceptions surrounding motivation can sometimes leave us feeling helpless in supporting them effectively.</p>

        <p>It is commonly believed that motivation is solely synonymous with excitement, high energy, or joy. While these feelings may accompany high motivation for some, for others it is not the case. Understanding the true essence of motivation is crucial in empowering patients to embark on their journey of change.</p>

        <p>Join us as we hear from Professor Liz Rieger, a distinguished clinical psychologist and researcher at The Australian National University. In this insightful video, Professor Rieger unravels the complexity of motivation, defining its cognitive nature and exploring the two fundamental components that drive behavior change.</p>

